<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Verse 1 (M1-8): "33" for ①, "43" for ①¹ at M5; Gm7 with "233" for color M3
- Verse 2 (M9-16): repeat with "43" ①¹ at opening (variety); quartal Gm at M11
- Bridge (M17-24): Am/Dm/Gm/C7 sequence — LH expands to 4 notes; Am "333" for emotional peak; FΔ7 = maj7 adds color
- Coda (M25-32): Bø7 dim quality at M27; strongest V7 LH voicing C7 at M28; final climax I "334" F2-C3-F3-A3

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- M3→4: Bb4 common tone between Gm7 and I
- M20: C7 — LH has complete 4-note dominant 7th: C2 G2 Bb2 E3
- M22: chromatic bass line Dm→Bb→Am tracks well-known 16th-century progression
- M27: Bø7 (E°7 sub) provides extra tension before C7 resolution

TEXTURE ARC:
- Verse 1: light — RH 2 notes, LH 3 notes
- Verse 2: slight growth — occasional 3-note RH, LH arpeggio motion
- Bridge: climax — Am 4-note LH, FΔ7 sparkle
- Coda: dramatic — Gm7/C7/Bø7 sequence; final ① "334" full close
-->
